HEADWORD: Caperberry
<hw>Ca"per*ber`ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
small olive-shaped berry of the European and Oriental caper, said to be
used in pickles and as a condiment.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The currantlike fruit of the African and Arabian
caper (<spn>Capparis sodado</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Caper tree</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Caper bush</ent>⟦br⟧
